285 g Top Sirloin Steak
227 g Fresh Linguine
237 mL Cream
¼ cup Parmesan Cheese, shredded
1 unit(s) Garlic, cloves
56 g Yellow Onion, chopped
1 unit(s) Beef Broth Concentrate
7 g Chives
113 g Mushrooms
20 g Cream Sauce Spice Blend
4 tbsp Unsalted Butter*
1 tbsp Oil*
0.13 tsp Salt*
0.13 tsp Pepper*

Before starting, preheat the broiler to high.
Bring a large pot of salted water to a boil (use same for 4 servings).
Wash and dry all produce.
Quarter mushrooms.
Thinly slice chives.
Peel, then mince or grate the garlic.
Pat steaks dry with paper towels. Season with salt and pepper.

Heat a large non-stick pan over medium-high. When hot, add 1 tbsp (2 tbsp) oil, then steaks. Pan-fry for 2-3 min per side.
Transfer steaks to an unlined baking sheet. Roast in the middle of the oven for 5-8 min, until cooked to desired doneness.**

Meanwhile, to the boiling water, add linguine. Cook for 2-3 min, until tender but still firm to the bite.
Reserve 1/2 cup (1 cup) pasta water. Strain linguine, then return to the pot, off heat.
Add 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter and half the chives. Toss to coat.

Reheat the same pan over medium heat.
When hot, add 2 tbsp (4 tbsp) butter, then mushrooms and onions. Cook for 5-6 min, stirring occasionally, until softened.
Sprinkle Cream Sauce Spice Blend and garlic over top veggies. Cook for 1 min, stirring often until coated.
Add broth concentrate, cream, 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) salt and 1/4 tsp (1/2 tsp) pepper. Cook for 1-2 min, stirring often until sauce thickens slightly.

Thinly slice steaks.
To the large pot with noodles, add mushroom cream sauce. Toss to coat. (NOTE: If the pasta is dry, slowly add reserved pasta water until desired consistency is reached.)
Divide pasta between bowls, then top with the steak.
Sprinkle Parmesan and remaining chives over top.